1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,294
<i>Where did you hide the money?</i>

2
00:00:03,378 --> 00:00:05,005
<i>- Where?!</i>
- [JACINTO]<i> Wait!</i>

3
00:00:05,088 --> 00:00:07,257
[JACINTO GROANS]
<i>On the island.</i>

4
00:00:07,340 --> 00:00:08,174
<i>Where exactly?</i>

5
00:00:08,258 --> 00:00:09,676
<i>At the staff house.</i>

6
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:11,594
<i>You're easy to talk to.</i>

7
00:00:11,678 --> 00:00:13,680
<i>And because of that, you're off the hook.</i>

8
00:00:13,763 --> 00:00:16,474
<i>After all, if it weren't for you,</i>

9
00:00:17,434 --> 00:00:21,980
<i>there wouldn't have been</i>
<i>a hostage taking at La Playa Roja.</i>

10
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:23,523
<i>Yes.</i>

11
00:00:23,606 --> 00:00:25,900
<i>He's the mastermind.</i>

12
00:00:25,984 --> 00:00:28,445
<i>The real boss of all of us.</i>

13
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:29,654
<i>It's not me.</i>

14
00:00:31,531 --> 00:00:34,325
<i>- Come on! Grab him.</i>
<i>- Wait. Wait!</i>

15
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:36,953
- [JACINTO SCREAMS]
- [PEOPLE EXCLAIMING, SHOUTING]

16
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:40,040
[EMIL]<i> There. The cops can't say</i>
<i>we didn't keep our word.</i>

17
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:42,917
<i>We'll send them to La Playa Roja.</i>

18
00:00:43,001 --> 00:00:45,336
<i>The task is simple.</i>

19
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:50,049
<i>Get our money and jewelry from the island.</i>

20
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:53,052
<i>If you don't return by twelve noon…</i>

21
00:00:55,638 --> 00:00:57,348
<i>we'll kill all of them.</i>

22
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:04,939
<i>We've prepared a vehicle</i>
<i>for you to get to the port,</i>

23
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:07,859
<i>and a boat for you to get to the island.</i>

24
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:11,029
<i>Don't mind the cops.</i>

25
00:01:11,112 --> 00:01:13,323
<i>I've talked to General Cabral.</i>

26
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:15,075
<i>If someone tries to interfere with you,</i>

27
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:17,160
<i>I'll show them what I'm capable of again.</i>

28
00:01:19,871 --> 00:01:22,624
I've been wanting to ask if you're okay.

29
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:26,628
Even though I know you're not.

30
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:30,465
How could I be okay, Liam?

31
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:34,302
I never even thought of my mother
doing what she did.

32
00:01:34,385 --> 00:01:38,264
Everyone makes mistakes, bro.

33
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:43,603
It's that easy for you, Liam?

34
00:01:45,104 --> 00:01:46,189
To forgive?

35
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:52,445
You and I didn't talk for years
before all this happened.

36
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:59,077
<i>You jerk!</i>

37
00:01:59,661 --> 00:02:04,833
Before all of this, I was furious at Papa.

38
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,000
You know that.

39
00:02:09,838 --> 00:02:12,382
[LIAM] <i>I blamed him</i>
<i>for what happened to Mama.</i>

40
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:17,470
<i>I even blamed him for</i>
<i>the hostage situation.</i>

41
00:02:18,596 --> 00:02:19,556
Because--

42
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:20,890
[OLSEN] Because…

43
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:24,853
Ayen's father just wanted revenge.

44
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,648
So technically,

45
00:02:29,899 --> 00:02:32,068
this is all Dad's fault, right?

46
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:41,870
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:02:49,043 --> 00:02:50,545
If that's the case,

48
00:02:50,628 --> 00:02:53,882
then technically, you were right before.

49
00:02:53,965 --> 00:02:55,425
I'm at fault too.

50
00:02:57,719 --> 00:03:02,724
I knew there was something going on
between them, and I did nothing.

51
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,893
That's on me too.

52
00:03:04,976 --> 00:03:06,769
That's why I blamed you.

53
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,065
But, bro, that's over.

54
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:12,817
It's done.

55
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:16,321
I'm done blaming you

56
00:03:17,322 --> 00:03:18,531
or Papa.

57
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:23,995
When Mama and I were in danger…

58
00:03:27,457 --> 00:03:31,753
and I saw how willing Dad was
to sacrifice his own life for us…

59
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:36,341
all my anger disappeared.

60
00:03:39,260 --> 00:03:41,012
All my resentment.

61
00:03:42,805 --> 00:03:45,975
Like I said, if anything good
came out of all this,

62
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:49,062
it's that we became whole again.

63
00:03:50,146 --> 00:03:51,481
The three of us.

64
00:03:54,776 --> 00:03:56,402
As a family.

65
00:03:56,486 --> 00:04:00,907
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:04:01,449 --> 00:04:02,951
So, bro,

67
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:08,706
I hope you and your mother…

68
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:14,504
I hope you can still forgive her.

69
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:19,050
We will do what Emil Padua wants.

70
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:22,220
We'll bring back his money.

71
00:04:24,013 --> 00:04:26,307
Not for him, but for our families.

72
00:04:26,391 --> 00:04:30,436
We'll find a way to save them.

73
00:04:31,187 --> 00:04:32,313
All of them.

74
00:04:33,731 --> 00:04:35,483
[OLSEN] We've done this before, right?

75
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:37,819
Of course.

76
00:04:37,902 --> 00:04:39,487
As long as we stick together.

77
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:41,322
And help each other.

78
00:04:43,032 --> 00:04:44,659
Just like brothers.

79
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:51,624
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

80
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:19,861
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

81
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:00,485
Sugar?

82
00:06:00,568 --> 00:06:02,361
You need sugar?

83
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:04,947
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

84
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:35,686
Greta, I just wanted to apologize.

85
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,188
I know.

86
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:40,483
Magnus already told me.

87
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:45,404
How many times did you deny it?

88
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:48,449
But then, when things got tight,
you suddenly took it back?

89
00:06:50,409 --> 00:06:51,619
What did you think?

90
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:56,374
That my husband would choose
your son over ours?

91
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:01,629
If you'd been in my place,

92
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:06,759
wouldn't you have done anything
to save your child too?

93
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:12,223
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

94
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:27,572
[LIAM GRUNTS]

95
00:07:29,365 --> 00:07:32,702
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

96
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:35,121
There's a path here
going to the staff house.

97
00:07:35,204 --> 00:07:36,247
Let's go.

98
00:07:53,097 --> 00:07:54,724
[EMIL] <i>I'll say it again.</i>

99
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:59,145
<i>If you don't return</i>
<i>with our cash and jewelry,</i>

100
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:02,231
<i>I'll kill them all.</i>

101
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:09,322
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

102
00:08:23,961 --> 00:08:30,927
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:08:49,779 --> 00:08:56,744
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

104
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:58,788
[LIAM GRUNTS]

105
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:00,873
[OLSEN] There's nothing here!

106
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:08,881
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

107
00:09:10,174 --> 00:09:11,884
It's not in the fridge!

108
00:09:15,721 --> 00:09:16,806
[LIAM] Nothing?

109
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:19,433
- They're crazy.
- It's all empty!

110
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:22,186
[PHONE RINGING]

111
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:29,110
Did you get our millions?

112
00:09:29,193 --> 00:09:32,154
There's nothing here! Jacinto fooled you!

113
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:33,656
<i>What do you mean, nothing?</i>

114
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:36,450
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:09:37,868 --> 00:09:39,954
<i>Are you trying to play games with me?</i>

116
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:40,913
<i>Where is it?</i>

117
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:42,331
There's really nothing here!

118
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:44,000
<i>Why would I lie to you?</i>

119
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:46,002
Look.

120
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:48,296
Where are your millions?

121
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:50,548
<i>Do you see them?</i>

122
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:52,925
<i>There's nothing, right?</i>

123
00:09:53,009 --> 00:09:54,218
<i>Don't get mad at us.</i>

124
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:56,345
We didn't trick you.

125
00:09:57,388 --> 00:09:59,181
I'll repeat this.

126
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:01,434
<i>I don't care.</i>

127
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:04,478
<i>Find our money</i>

128
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:09,358
<i>and bring it here by exactly twelve noon.</i>

129
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:11,569
<i>- Because if you don't…</i>
- [GRETA] <i>Can you stop?</i>

130
00:10:11,652 --> 00:10:13,863
What else do you expect them to do?

131
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:16,866
The money and jewelry
could already be with the police.

132
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:19,076
<i>Jacinto lied to you.</i>

133
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,329
<i>He didn't give the real location.</i>

134
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:28,711
I also believe Jacinto lied to us,
but I don't care.

135
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:32,798
<i>Turn the island over if you have to.</i>

136
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:36,135
<i>Just find our money</i>

137
00:10:36,218 --> 00:10:39,930
<i>and come back here by noon.</i>

138
00:10:40,014 --> 00:10:43,768
<i>Otherwise, this ends in bloodshed.</i>

139
00:10:43,851 --> 00:10:49,065
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

140
00:10:54,445 --> 00:10:57,448
What you're asking them
to do is impossible.

141
00:10:57,531 --> 00:10:59,825
It is a very large island.

142
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:01,827
I don't care.

143
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:11,087
[SIRENS WAILING]

144
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:14,382
<i>The body of Major Reynaldo Domingo</i>
<i>was recently found.</i>

145
00:11:14,465 --> 00:11:17,635
<i>He's suspected to be a victim</i>
<i>of summary execution.</i>

146
00:11:17,718 --> 00:11:23,140
<i>The crime is being linked to drug lords</i>
<i>allegedly operating in Alicante.</i>

147
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:25,142
Drug lords my ass, sir.

148
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:27,019
What do you think really happened?

149
00:11:28,729 --> 00:11:33,359
I'm sure it's connected to
the hostage taking at La Playa Roja.

150
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:36,070
Your godfather strongly suspected

151
00:11:36,153 --> 00:11:39,657
that Captain Jericho Jacinto was involved.

152
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:43,577
So it's not impossible
that the captain is connected to this.

153
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:46,122
- What's his condition?
- Critical, sir.

154
00:11:46,914 --> 00:11:48,374
He was brought here.

155
00:11:50,709 --> 00:11:52,086
He actually survived.

156
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,380
Bad weeds really do never die.

157
00:11:57,508 --> 00:11:58,509
[GROANS]

158
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:03,472
Sir, where are you going?

159
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:04,723
You're not well yet.

160
00:12:04,807 --> 00:12:06,058
Bring me my uniform.

161
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:15,234
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS]

162
00:12:23,742 --> 00:12:27,037
Maybe you could give them
a little more time?

163
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:29,957
What you're asking from them
is very difficult.

164
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,795
Or you can let me and my husband go.

165
00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:38,090
We know the ins and outs of the island.

166
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:39,842
We can help them find it.

167
00:12:39,925 --> 00:12:41,343
[CHUCKLES]

168
00:12:42,344 --> 00:12:44,138
You think I'm stupid?

169
00:12:44,221 --> 00:12:45,931
You just want to escape.

170
00:12:46,974 --> 00:12:48,058
Wait!

171
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,770
How much money is it anyway?

172
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:53,898
300 million?

173
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:56,442
I can raise that.

174
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:57,943
Just give me time.

175
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:03,282
[HOSTAGE TAKERS LAUGH]

176
00:13:09,079 --> 00:13:11,540
Stop playing games with me, Senator.

177
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:15,628
You just gave us 100 million cash.

178
00:13:15,711 --> 00:13:18,422
I know you're broke.

179
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:21,675
Which is why you're running
for office again, remember?

180
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:23,886
To keep the cash flowing?

181
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:27,681
I don't care how corrupt you are.

182
00:13:28,682 --> 00:13:32,770
You're just unlucky that
your son was at La Playa Roja

183
00:13:32,853 --> 00:13:38,567
and he got dragged into
what Magnus Roja did to me.

184
00:13:39,276 --> 00:13:43,113
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYS]

185
00:13:45,908 --> 00:13:50,955
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

186
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:56,043
He's just messing with us!

187
00:13:56,877 --> 00:14:00,381
Where on this huge island
will we find his cash and jewelry?

188
00:14:00,464 --> 00:14:01,840
We should still try.

189
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,510
How, then?

190
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:09,348
Check the staff house.

191
00:14:09,431 --> 00:14:11,517
Search all the rooms in there.

192
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,602
I'll check the villas.

193
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:16,772
Then, we'll meet up here, okay?

194
00:14:16,855 --> 00:14:18,440
See you in a bit!

195
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:25,030
[FRUSTRATED SCREAM]

196
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:38,252
[DOCTOR] It was a serious fall.

197
00:14:38,335 --> 00:14:40,212
His injuries are life-threatening.

198
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:42,882
He suffered from multiple grave fractures.

199
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:46,343
But luckily, no cranial fractures.

200
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:49,930
He has significant head trauma.
That's why he's still unconscious.

201
00:14:50,014 --> 00:14:52,933
He will remain under close observation.

202
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:55,102
- I have to go.
- Thank you, Doc.

203
00:14:55,811 --> 00:14:56,896
Sarge.

204
00:15:00,107 --> 00:15:02,818
Get me all available information
on Captain Jacinto.

205
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:06,572
I want to know what connection
he has with Emil Padua,

206
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:08,616
and who his other accomplices are.

207
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:13,954
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYS]

208
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:21,795
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:26,967
[GRUNTS]

210
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:36,852
Where could it be?

211
00:15:45,861 --> 00:15:49,657
Tell them why they're here.

212
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:54,703
Tell them what kind of nonsense
you got up to

213
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,538
to make them all end up here!

214
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:06,090
He ruined my daughter's life!

215
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:11,512
He made her his mistress
and then abandoned her!

216
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:18,310
[SCOFFS]

217
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:22,856
That's not all.
Because of you Rojas, we lost our land.

218
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:25,442
You evicted us.

219
00:16:25,526 --> 00:16:28,696
But that land wasn't yours.
You were just squatting there.

220
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:32,074
- We are the actual owners.
- So what?

221
00:16:32,157 --> 00:16:33,784
We'd lived there our entire lives!

222
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:37,496
Magnus Roja also harmed me.

223
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:43,585
Because you stuck your nose in,

224
00:16:45,254 --> 00:16:47,214
my brother and I went to jail.

225
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:49,550
Who's your brother?

226
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:51,135
Homer.

227
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:55,180
Homer Sebastian.

228
00:16:55,931 --> 00:16:59,977
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

229
00:17:02,938 --> 00:17:03,939
<i>Homer Sebastian?</i>

230
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:07,526
<i>You're under arrest for gun smuggling</i>
<i>and illegal arms trading.</i>

231
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:09,236
<i>You have the right to remain silent.</i>

232
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:12,281
<i>Whatever you say can and will</i>
<i>be used against you in court.</i>

233
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:15,451
<i>- Stop resisting.</i>
<i>- Ow!</i>

234
00:17:15,534 --> 00:17:17,244
<i>- Arms behind you.</i>
<i>- You're hurting me!</i>

235
00:17:17,327 --> 00:17:18,912
[HOMER] <i>Ouch!</i>

236
00:17:19,830 --> 00:17:20,914
[GROANS]

237
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:24,585
<i>You got the wrong guy!</i>

238
00:17:24,668 --> 00:17:25,627
<i>Hey!</i>

239
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:28,672
[LUCAS] Homer's boss was a VIP
at your resort.

240
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:32,718
You found out they were involved in
gun-smuggling operations.

241
00:17:32,801 --> 00:17:36,430
And you were the one
who called the cops on them.

242
00:17:37,848 --> 00:17:39,683
He got arrested.

243
00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:41,560
And so did I.

244
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,481
And so were our colleagues.

245
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:47,608
You ruined our business.

246
00:17:47,691 --> 00:17:50,277
You ruined

247
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:51,904
our lives.

248
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:55,324
Speechless now?

249
00:17:57,242 --> 00:17:58,660
- [SCREAMS]
- [GROANS IN PAIN]

250
00:17:58,744 --> 00:18:00,996
That's enough!

251
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:04,792
[COUGHS, GROANS]

252
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,628
I know something.

253
00:18:07,711 --> 00:18:10,297
I think I might know where…

254
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:13,342
where they hid what you're looking for.

255
00:18:14,176 --> 00:18:15,552
How come you know?

256
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:18,180
When I saw Jacinto on the island,

257
00:18:18,972 --> 00:18:20,766
he was going to shoot my son,

258
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:23,143
but I shot him first.

259
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:27,314
But before that, I heard him.

260
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:30,067
He was talking to one of your men.

261
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:32,277
He mentioned a place.

262
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:36,240
What you're looking for
might be hidden there.

263
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:40,953
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYS]

264
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,876
Where?

265
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:53,132
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYS]

266
00:18:54,758 --> 00:19:01,098
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

267
00:19:06,019 --> 00:19:07,062
[GRUNTS]

268
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:24,621
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

269
00:19:26,456 --> 00:19:27,291
[CLICKS]

270
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:29,793
<i>It's not a real gun.</i>

271
00:19:33,922 --> 00:19:40,888
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:19:54,943 --> 00:20:01,909
[MUSIC TURNS SOMBER]

273
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:27,476
<i>Chief Lo! Where's Mama's boyfriend?</i>

274
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:29,478
<i>There we go.</i>

275
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,438
<i>See?</i>

276
00:20:32,272 --> 00:20:33,523
<i>He's here too.</i>

277
00:20:34,316 --> 00:20:35,359
[CHUCKLES]

278
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:38,779
<i>Chief Lo brought him along</i>
<i>when he came here.</i>

279
00:20:38,862 --> 00:20:40,280
<i>He almost forgot though.</i>

280
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:43,617
<i>Yeah.</i>

281
00:20:44,493 --> 00:20:45,994
<i>When we save enough money,</i>

282
00:20:46,578 --> 00:20:49,164
<i>we'll bury him somewhere proper.</i>

283
00:20:49,998 --> 00:20:52,334
<i>To keep his soul at peace.</i>

284
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:56,755
<i>We can't just carry him around</i>
<i>wherever we go.</i>

285
00:20:58,131 --> 00:20:59,883
I'll leave you here for a bit, okay, Pa?

286
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:02,970
I'll come back for you.

287
00:21:03,762 --> 00:21:05,472
- [DOOR OPENS] I didn't find--
- Liam!

288
00:21:05,555 --> 00:21:06,390
[OLSEN SCREAMS]

289
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:08,850
You startled me!

290
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:10,310
I dropped Papa!

291
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:13,563
Are those your father's ashes?

292
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:18,443
Are you sure these are ashes?

293
00:21:26,451 --> 00:21:28,203
I don't think so.

294
00:21:34,876 --> 00:21:35,919
Sand?

295
00:21:38,046 --> 00:21:39,339
But why?

296
00:21:40,882 --> 00:21:45,762
[SOFT, DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

297
00:21:56,106 --> 00:21:57,816
[MIKE] <i>That leads straight</i>
<i>to the maintenance passage.</i>

298
00:21:57,899 --> 00:21:59,151
<i>Enough for an escape run.</i>

299
00:21:59,234 --> 00:22:01,820
<i>You're close to dying,</i>
<i>but you're still useful.</i>

300
00:22:01,903 --> 00:22:03,572
<i>You put her in even more danger.</i>

301
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:05,574
<i>Just do what you need to do.</i>

302
00:22:05,657 --> 00:22:07,909
<i>Why was Papa's urn filled with sand?</i>

303
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:11,455
<i>It'll be far worse if we're not back</i>
<i>by twelve with their money.</i>

304
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:13,332
<i>Do you know Homer personally?</i>

305
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:16,001
[HOMER] <i>Magnus Roja and I</i>
<i>still have unfinished business.</i>

306
00:22:16,793 --> 00:22:18,670
<i>- Son?</i>
<i>- You know where the money is?</i>

307
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:21,465
[GRETA] <i>You don't have much time.</i>
<i>Just listen to me.</i>

308
00:22:23,842 --> 00:22:24,926
<i>What's that?</i>

309
00:22:26,928 --> 00:22:27,846
<i>Relax.</i>
